cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual perception and recognition. The use of Deep Belief Nets also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the estimation of albedo and surface normals, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on illumination variations and light sources could also place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
